The wife of an Australian podiatrist who was found stabbed seven times in the Bahamas is being questioned by police in relation to his death.

The body of Phillip Vasyli, 59, was found inside his home in exclusive gated community Old Fort Bay on New Providence Island.

Local police said the married father-of-two had been dead for seven hours before a worker found him, 9News reported.

